title: SQL vs. NoSQL
content: MySQL is a relational data model, where NoSQL is a nonrelational data model that allows for more flexibility in data storage. Oracle and MySQL are examples of SQL databases. MongoDB and DynamoDB are examples of nonrelational databases.

title: Javascript Data Types
content: Programming languages have built-in data structures. The primitive values in javascript are immutable and represented at the lowest level of the language. They include: boolean, null, undefined, number, bigint, string, and symbol.
